Author: YogSothoth
Content: Three prisoners were sitting in a U.S. jail, found guilty of "economic crimes" and were also comparing stories. The first one said, "I charged higher prices than my competitors, and I was found guilty of profiteering, monopolizing and exploiting consumers." The second one said, "I charged lower prices than my competitors, and I was found guilty of predatory pricing, cutthroat competing and under-charging." The third prisoner said, "I charged the same prices as my competitors, and I was found guilty of collusion, price leadership and cartelization."

Author: psyklic
Content:
In my experience, books provide higher-quality tutorials to subjects than anything online. Not only that, but all of the information is in one place, saving you the time of searching through the masses of poorly-written and incomplete online tutorials.

However, online is better than reference books. It also has more information on the latest trends and practices. But, you must be a very active reader to even know where to look for the latest information. And, you need to be very knowledgeable in the field to filter good posts from bad.
